FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1782857895
OL,3,CWoman dies after alligator bites her
OL,4,Carm off in Florida
OL,6,FHowever, any alligator measuring over
OL,7,F6 feet poses a threat, and males
OL,8,Ftypically can reach around 14 feet in
OL,9,Flength when fully grown.
OL,11,FTheir danger to humans is increased if
OL,12,Fthey feel threatened, are protecting
OL,13,Ftheir nest, or are habituated to being
OL,14,Ffed by people.
OL,16,FAlligators that have lost their fear
OL,17,Fof humans, associating them with free
OL,18,Ffood, are far more dangerous than wild
OL,19,Falligators who are not used to human
OL,20,Fpresence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
